<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 26 at 4:43PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Blowing and drifting snow through this evening...
Areas of blowing and drifting snow will affect the northern Rocky
Mountain front region, including areas around East Glacier Park,
St Mary and Babb, through this evening. This includes portions of
Highway 2 from just west of Browning to Marias Pass.
Visibility could be reduced at times, and snow drifts are possible
on roadways.
Those traveling in this region should be prepared for slippery
road conditions and areas of poor visibility.</description>
